 of liberal Romantic ideology. Susan Kirkpatrick examines the textual representations that link liberal ideology, Romantic configurations of subjectivity, and women's writing, in an exciting revelation of early nineteenth-century gender consciousness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLiterature and societyzSpain. 0aRomanticismzSpain. 0aSelf in literature. 0aSpanish literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aSpanish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSubjectivity in literature. 0aWomen and literaturezSpainxHistoryy19th century. 4aRomanticism. 4aSpain. 4aSpanish literature. 4acultural history. 4ahistory of literature. 4ahistory. 4aideology. 4aliterary movements. 4aliterature. 4apresent. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052033558540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052033559240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520335592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520335592/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles